The paper discusses the development and evolution of malware, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the process of community succession and coevolution, which can be viewed as a complex system (cs.SI) and software engineering (cs.SE) problem. The paper also mentions the varying modes of transmission and adaptability of malware, which can be studied using data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
